02f5_920x584.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:584,&quot;width&quot;:920,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:217277,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;Note: The title of this post is a METAPHOR. As far as we know, all physical processes in the Universe obey both the laws of electromagnetism AND the laws of thermodynamics, in aggregate. If you have a very small number of particles, either set of laws can be violated for a short time, but that has nothing to do with what this post is talking about. This post title is METAPHORICAL -- it is about how technologies discovered through the application of electromagnetism are becoming more useful to society, often at the expense of technologies discovered (or at least, explained) through application of thermodynamics. I HOPE THAT CLEARS THINGS UP&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="Note: The title of this post is a METAPHOR. As far as we know, all physical processes in the Universe obey both the laws of electromagnetism AND the laws of thermodynamics, in aggregate. If you have a very small number of particles, either set of laws can be violated for a short time, but that has nothing to do with what this post is talking about. This post title is METAPHORICAL -- it is about how technologies discovered through the application of electromagnetism are becoming more useful to society, often at the expense of technologies discovered (or at least, explained) through application of thermodynamics. I HOPE THAT CLEARS THINGS UP" title="注意：这篇文章的标题是一个隐喻。据我们所知，宇宙中的所有物理过程总体上都遵循电磁定律和热力学定律。如果粒子数量非常少，则可能会在短时间内违反任何一组定律，但这与本文讨论的内容无关。这篇文章的标题是隐喻性的——它是关于通过应用电磁学发现的技术如何变得对社会更有用，通常是以牺牲通过应用热力学发现（或至少解释）的技术为代价的。我希望事情能够澄清" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3029a450-6d3e-4d43-a5e5-65d4e98302f5_920x584.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3029a450-6d3e-4d43-a5e5-65d4e98302f5_920x584.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3029a450-6d3e-4d43-a5e5-65d4e98302f5_920x584.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3029a450-6d3e-4d43-a5e5-65d4e98302f5_920x584.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></figure></div><p>今天我想咆哮一场技术革命。</p><p>我写了很多关于<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/decade-of-the-battery-334">电池的兴起</a>、<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/at-least-five-interesting-things-84f">绿色能源的胜利</a>以及 2020 年代发生的其他<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/techno-optimism-for-2024">技术革命</a>等内容。但其中许多发展都是相互关联的。我认为它们是一种深刻而根本的转变的明显突出，几乎很难描述它。这是关于整个人类技术所基于的基本物理过程的转变。</p><p>我记得当我十几岁的时候，和我的朋友们一起看动画片<a href="https://gizmodo.com/why-robotech-is-the-greatest-love-story-of-the-20th-cen-5971053">《太空堡垒》</a> （距离它首次发布已经很多年了；我还没有<em>那么</em>老！）。剧中存在着一种秘密的超强能源，叫做“原始文化”。我记得我的一位朋友问：“你如何从原始文化中获得能量？另一位朋友说：“好吧，首先你用原始文化将水煮成蒸汽，然后用它来转动涡轮机……”</p><p>我们都笑了，但这个笑话深深植根于技术现实。直到今天，大多数能源——包括核能——基本上只是<em>加热水</em>，将水变成蒸汽，推动某种轮子，A) 转动一些齿轮使机器运转，或者 B) 转动一个轮子。产生电流的磁铁。对于化石燃料能源（尽管不是核能），这涉及<em>燃烧</em>——化学反应快速释放热量。</p><p>燃烧是人类提取和运输能量的两种主要方法之一。了解如何利用燃烧可能是人类历史上最重要的技术革命。煤动力蒸汽机和石油动力内燃机提供的能源创造了机械化农业、现代制造业、铁路运输、汽车、卡车、现代航运、动力飞行以及大多数事物。这使人类摆脱了我们开始时的赤贫泥沼。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg" width="652" height="463.4313725490196" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:725,&quot;width&quot;:1020,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:652,&quot;bytes&quot;:107796,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F42571286-a0a4-4cfd-9c3d-e5361f51f668_1020x725.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>但与此同时，第二次技术革命也正在发生，它也改变了我们世界的面貌。这就是<em>电</em>——通过导电材料移动电子的能力。</p><p>电力和燃烧是相辅相成的——例如，当你燃烧煤炭来煮水，从而转动涡轮机来转动发电机来发电时。当然，两者都依赖某种形式的化学势能——油箱、电池等——将储存的能量从一个地方传输到另一个地方。</p><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-triumph-of-electromagnetism-over">阅读更多</a></p>; 
